South African vocal band "Ladysmith Black Mambazo", with lead vocal Shabalala (C,) perform 02 July 2002 during a concert in Madrid . JOHANNESBURG - Tributes are pouring in for legendary Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala. The 78-year-old lead singer died on Tuesday morning after a long illness. READ: Ladysmith Black Mambazo founder Joseph Shabalala dies After five decades as an active musician, Shabalala announced his retirement in 2013. Ladysmith Black Mamba has toured the world sharing the stage with international stars. Below is a list of the group's most popular songs: Paul Simon - Diamonds On The Soles Of Her Shoes ft Ladysmith Black Mambazo Check out the official music video for "Diamonds On The Soles Of Her Shoes" by Paul Simon Ladysmith Black Mambazo - Hello My Baby Paul Simon - Graceland : The African Tour Ladysmith Black Mambazo perform Homeless Live